MatchedRegions.transcript: The focus of our paper is on the macro search space for neural architecture search.
Now, traditional cell-based approach restricts the search to decide the operation and structure of a single block only, then the same block is repeated to form an end-to-end model.
macrosurface enables the individual search for each macroblock in a DNN, leading to better performance.
However, it is expensive because the subspace size grows exponentially with the number of blocks.
To provide a systematic study of the performance of North's algorithm on a macro surface, we release blocks for a first large-scale benchmark and study of a macro surface.
